		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=73&FN=Wizard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1878064&TN=Solo%27in+a+Wizzy+%281%2D40%29&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1878064&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1"> First let me say this should not be tried for those with a faint heart, or in a hurry. I play a HIE on the Torv server.<BR>1-4 Felwithe's newbe zone (Home Sweet Home)<BR>5-8 I learned to kite orc's from the orc hill area. By zapping them running back to a safe spot near the guards at Orc Lift,  rooting and finshing off. <BR>8-9 Tried Crushbone, after several BAD groups and nasty CR's (back then you had to find and retrieve your body reguardless). I decided to solo only. When running into Butcher to turn in CB belt's I started to hang out at the Crossroads in butcher<BR>9-15 Butcher, by using the guards at the crossroads to med-up. I made many friends in passing. "twas alway's a great place to catch buffs from passerby's" and the loot's not bad. Played there long e'nuff to know just when the Orc Runner or Qued would pop. (pre Aqua goblin dayz).. the Zone was always friendly<BR>16-21 Oasis of Marr. here I hunted the zoneline. My sweet spot had a high peak that I could get up on and use Wizzy sight to watch for certain mobs and to keep an eye on any SG's in the area. This is where I perfected my wizzy pulling skills by nuking a mob running back to the safty of the zone line to my back & root & nuke. I did well here, killed a gazillion spiders, e'nuff to tailor skill up and sell stacks of swatches (time to up-grade armour). It was also when I joined a guild <BR>22-28 Lake of Ill Omen let's title this part, "The Tough Years" Lake of Ill Omen. some guildies said that was the place to be. so I stuck it out. I found a spot near the Windmill that was a safe med spot. with the gates I now had I was able to gate to safty when things went bad. like adds, need I say more?. at lvl 28 I hit a nightmare lvl. even hunting lite blues was tough. I was then my guild helped out, by attending a couple of raids I dinged 29. Now I've got Bonds of Force, nuff said. At this time I bought the Luclin expansion. Ahh the moon and all the possiblities, <BR>29-32 Marus Seru, first greyhoppers, then when I needed no more hides for tailoring, Stonegrabbers, and everthing else that moved.<BR>33-35 shared exp between Dawnshroud's S'rooms and Butcher, "crazed gobbies"<BR>36-41 North Karana. I now own Hill Giants and Griffons, by standing on the guard tower hill I can use wizzy sight and nearly see the whole zone the Exp is slow, but the loot rocks &  I've never been in to big of a hurry to lvl anyway<BR>  I've really enjoyed playing this wizzy and solo'in has made her always cap off  skill lvl,  before I've lvl up. although I've not done many quest, I have done the research quest made a pile of pratice runes and currently research is 140, baking 138, tailoring 135, smithing 60, and with almost 4000pp banked. (Saving up for a horsy)I can't complain. (soon to be a year old in RL time) I've played her 56+ days OMG<BR> well thar's my history.. I've been told several times wizzy's can't solo. he he..  I plan soloing to my 45 season, then get down to lace & brass tacks and help out my guild.. safe journeys<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
