		<hr size="1">Nemri Zek, one big mistake in your post. Wizards/druids THE best soloers? Sure, they can solo 4 blues, maybe even 4 evens/yellows at a time (with a ridiculous amount of downtime I might add), but what ub3r mobs can they solo. Ahh, it must be hard to have a simple number of damage that you know you can do. even if you somehow manage to use your most effecient dd over and over without root breaking once, you still can only do a set amount of damage. 3500 mana? Thats probably the max you could get, I might be wrong. 3500 mana calculates into a precise number of hitpoints gone.</P><P>Meanwhile you have the shaman. If you are going for efficiency, resist debuff, 70% slow (which will get you the aggro), dot, dot, dot, root, back up and pull back pet (or you can let him die if you choose), med, re-root/dot as necessary. Plus, with the mob slowed and your buffed ac, you can tank mobs for the amount of time it takes to dot/root.</P><P>I'm not dissing wizards in any way, I think they are cool. I would just like you to put your thoughts into the right perspective. Sure you can solo 4 things. But can you solo things that would take an entire 60+ group to take out? WW dragons anyone?</P><P>Eilderts-24 iksar shaman on Morell-Thul<BR>Dirty South, East Coast!<BR>Class of 05!<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
